description:
  Let A,K be positive integers and u=-2,-1,1 or 2. The main contribution of the
paper is a proof that each of the D(u^2)-triples {K,A^2K+2uA,(A+1)^2K+2u(A+1)}
has unique extension to a D(u^2)-quadruple.

Comment: 4 pages, 3 figures, in press, New Frontiers in Black Hole
  Astrophysics. Proceedings IAU Symposium No 324, 2017. Andreja Gomboc \&
  Carole Mundell, eds.}
